File: The SA Human Rights Commission said schools need clean water, sanitation, training and personal protective equipment for teachers and learners. JOHANNESBURG - Various teaching unions and the schools governing body association have welcomed the reopening of schools on Monday. It follows a meeting with Basic Education Minister, Angie Motshekga earlier. READ: Schools ready to open come Monday: Angie Motshekga The department has handed over a report showing that schools' overall readiness is at 94-percent. The unions have given the reopening their blessing based on the report, as well as the understanding that schools that aren't ready, will remain closed. Grade 7 and 12 pupils are the first batch to return. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.